8276,-0.12527908,0.00122476,0.034617,0.20198143,0.05144099,0.04640661,0.01771145,-0.09114607,0.02469572,0.06385289,-0.02968421,-0.01317883,0.02444884,0.05774762,-0.06142458,0.05732739,-0.00034895,-0.05771801,-0.02740836,0.01082253,-0.03923142,0.04403348,-0.00599729,-0.02570167,-0.03855471,0.10614021,-0.02465275,-0.01807027,-0.01242132,-0.00155831,0.04702752,-0.02334076,0.00636733,-0.05594139,0.00743865,0.01180693,0.00025162,-0.00396612,-0.02278326,0.00258167,-0.01630528,0.02543238,-0.02908832,-0.031109,0.15054935,0.04373516],"last_embed":{"hash":"101acdj","tokens":433}}},"last_read":{"hash":"101acdj","at":1774951890627},"class_name":"SmartSource","last_import":{"mtime":1774951821388,"size":2542,"at":1774951884801,"hash":"101acdj"},"blocks":{"#---frontmatter---":[1,57],"#Unconventional transcriptional response to environmental enrichment in a mouse model of Rett syndrome":[59,63],"#Unconventional transcriptional response to environmental enrichment in a mouse model of Rett syndrome#{1}":[61,63]},"outlinks":[{"title":"Author/Bredford Kerr","target":"Author/Bredford Kerr","line":45},{"title":"Author/Bredford Kerr","target":"Author/Bredford Kerr","line":46},{"title":"Author/Pamela A. Silva","target":"Author/Pamela A. Silva","line":47},{"title":"Author/Pamela Silva","target":"Author/Pamela Silva","line":48},{"title":"Author/Katherina Walz","target":"Author/Katherina Walz","line":49},{"title":"Author/Katherina Walz","target":"Author/Katherina Walz","line":50},{"title":"Author/Juan I. Young","target":"Author/Juan I. Young","line":51},{"title":"Author/Juan I. Young","target":"Author/Juan I. Young","line":52},{"title":"PDF","target":"biblib/kerr_unconventional_2010/kerr_unconventional_2010.pdf","line":54}],"metadata":{"id":"kerr_unconventional_2010","type":"article-journal","title":"Unconventional transcriptional response to environmental enrichment in a mouse model of Rett syndrome","issued":{"date-parts":[[2010]]},"DOI":"10.1371/journal.pone.0011534","container-title":"PLOS ONE","abstract":"Background Rett syndrome (RTT) is an X-linked postnatal neurodevelopmental disorder caused by mutations in the gene encoding methyl-CpG binding protein 2 (MeCP2) and one of the leading causes of mental retardation in females. RTT is characterized by psychomotor retardation, purposeless hand movements, autistic-like behavior and abnormal gait. We studied the effects of environmental enrichment (EE) on the phenotypic manifestations of a RTT mouse model that lacks MeCP2 (Mecp2−/y). Principal Findings We found that EE delayed and attenuated some neurological alterations presented by Mecp2−/y mice and prevented the development of motor discoordination and anxiety-related abnormalities. To define the molecular correlate of this beneficial effect of EE, we analyzed the expression of several synaptic marker genes whose expression is increased by EE in several mouse models. Conclusions/Significance We found that EE induced downregulation of several synaptic markers, suggesting that the partial prevention of RTT-associated phenotypes is achieved through a non-conventional transcriptional program.","tags":["#literature_note"],"author":[{"family":"Kerr","given":"Bredford","literal":""},{"family":"Kerr","given":"Bredford","literal":""},{"family":"Silva","given":"Pamela A.","literal":""},{"family":"Silva","given":"Pamela","literal":""},{"family":"Walz","given":"Katherina","literal":""},{"family":"Walz","given":"Katherina","literal":""},{"family":"Young","given":"Juan I.","literal":""},{"family":"Young","given":"Juan I.","literal":""}],"citation-key":"kerr_unconventional_2010","year":"2010","dateCreated":"2026-03-31","reading-status":"to-read","aliases":["Unconventional transcriptional response to environmental enrichment in a mouse model of Rett syndrome"],"author-links":["[[Author/Bredford Kerr]]","[[Author/Bredford Kerr]]","[[Author/Pamela A. Silva]]","[[Author/Pamela Silva]]","[[Author/Katherina Walz]]","[[Author/Katherina Walz]]","[[Author/Juan I. Young]]",